SIMPLE: synergist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synergist
<hw>Syn"er*gist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>synergiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who holds the
doctrine of synergism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A remedy which has an action
similar to that of another remedy, and hence increases the efficiency of
that remedy when combined with it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 3. (Biochemistry) A chemical compound which exhibits a
synergistic effect on some biochemical or physiological action, in
combination with another compound. [A supertype of def. 2.] -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synergistic</ent>⟦br⟧
